title: Test feature
message:
Test feature

Summary:
Add a "Test" feature to allow the user to test himself.
By pressing on "Start test", the user is given a set of 10 exercises and after he answers all the exercises, there should appear on the screen the percentage of correct answers.
Task: [[ https://phabricator.kde.org/T5288 | https://phabricator.kde.org/T5288 ]]

Test Plan:
1. Start an exercise.
2. Press on the "Start test" (next to "give up")
3. Answer all 10 questions
4. Start a new test or continue with normal questions

Reviewers: sandroandrade

Subscribers: stefant, sandroandrade

Tags: #minuet

Maniphest Tasks: T5288

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.kde.org/D4466

title: Bug - anchor to null on hover over the responses buttons (before beginning an exercise)
message:
Bug - anchor to null on hover over the responses buttons (before beginning an exercise)

Summary:
Steps to follow to replicate the bug:
1. open Minuet
2. open an exercise
3. before pressing "New Question", hover over the responses ("your choises") buttons
4. in the console, two "null" error will appear

[[ https://youtu.be/7hpGvvpUklU | link on Youtube ]]

Reviewers: sandroandrade

Subscribers: stefant

Tags: #minuet

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.kde.org/D4326

title: Change message text when pressing on GiveUp button
message:
Change message text when pressing on GiveUp button

Summary:
When pressing on GiveUp:
result: "Congratulations, you answered correctly!"
expected result: Another message (do not congratulate for giving up)

Now, when pressing on "GiveUp" button, "Here is the answer" is shown.

Reviewers: sandroandrade

Subscribers: stefant

Tags: #minuet

title: Pitch, Tempo and Volume using FluidSynth
message:
Pitch, Tempo and Volume using FluidSynth

Summary:
Use of the FluidSynth Library to set the pitch.
The documentations does mention that: 0 << **pitch** << 1024 * 16 - 1
The **pitch** **slider** has been set from 0 to 16
Changing the pitch has immediate effect.

The **tempo** has only been reactivated, it does work but needs the current question to be stopped() and played() again.

Reviewers: sandroandrade

Tags: #minuet

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.kde.org/D2713

title: Merge the play  and pause button
message:
Merge the play  and pause button

Instead of having two multimedia buttons, we can have the functionality with only one button with two states.
One state for play and other for pause.
Hence whenever they are called, a signal is sent to slot in MidiPlayer.qml.

title: Keep tempo factor settings across exercises playing
message:
Keep tempo factor settings across exercises playing

Unlike volume factor or pitch factor, the tempo factor was nowhere stored for the next song.
With this diff tempo factor will be stored and used when a new song is loaded.
